Crespi argues that manhua must be understood in the context of the pictorial magazines that hosted them, and in turn these magazines must be seen as important mediators of the modern urban experience. Even as times changed-from interwar-era consumerism to war-time mobilization to Mao-style propaganda-the art form adapted to stay on the cutting edge of both politics and style.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aCaricaturexPolitical aspectszChinay20th century. 0aCaricaturezChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aCaricatures and cartoonszChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aCommunism and culturezChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical culturezChinaxHistoryy20th century. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2020z9783110704655oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2020 Englishz978311070478508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520973862zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520973862zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520973862.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5 UC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070478-5 EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2020 E